reviewText: The low light, of this video, is just right. Peaceful, lovely ocean music.

Videos like this are super helpful when building better sleep habits (for me at least). According to the literature it's good to avoid extra stimulating media and especially avoid content with human faces as you try to wind down and send your body the message it's time to sleep soon.

I generally like the Window Channel videos, but not this one. I realize it's to help with sleep problems, but I found the picture quality to be lacking - I couldn't really see much beside an overexposed moon and a sliver of the shore. This COULD have been a good video, and is an excellent idea,  but it could have been done better.
I use this to help me sleep during the day, because I don't sleep at night. It's by far the best I've seen on Amazon. In less than 5 minutes I'm fast asleep. Love it!

Both the audio and the visual are very annoying.

The audio: They're crickets but after a while they sound like sleigh bells. Tiny little bells. Honestly, they're not too bad if I turn the sound down very low.

The visual: Watch the trailer. See the moon in the middle? Well, it is NOT dark. It is a like a flashlight in your bedroom. It is quite bright. If you like darkness (not totally dark) this will annoy the heck out of you. The way the video cycles, the clouds never cover it so it is continuously bright. If I am napping in the afternoon, it is not that bad at all but at nighttime, I cannot use it.

I have some trouble getting to sleep so trying the sleep help App seemed a reasonable choice I have been asked to comment on this by Amazon I have just started trying this and the rain App It's like looking out a window with the sounds of the outdoors or the sounds of rain falling, the scene is real and can be soothing. I rollover and adjust the volume low enough not to keep me awake set the sleep timer on my TV. It seems to work for me. If this shows me to be a successful relaxant I'll give a higher rating. Give these Apps a try it's can be worth it for you too.
